	/**   
	This is an OrGate on steroids.  Created 02/02/11 By: CMH (XENCOM Energy Management)
	This OrGate can be generated to accommodate any number of points. 

	1. Right Click on the program and Select "Action" then "VariableCount". Choose how many
	variables you would like to compare. (If you need more later, just increase the number.
	WARNING! If you decrease the number of slots, you could lose links. The program will
	start by deleting the highest number slot and continue until the correct amount of
	slots remain. You will not lose any slots that are less than the number requested.)

	2. Link your comparison values to the generated slots, and the module will start working.

	Note1:  If you delete a link while it is "true", the program will return the slot to "false";
	Note2:  If the linked point becomes inValid, it will not be used by the logic.
	Note3:  The Max number of variables you can add is 60.

	**/

	private int				count = 1;      
	private boolean			ValFlag1;
	private BStatusBoolean	InVal;


